<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05032o"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05032o">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05032o"> 32(o)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> soul of this particular / young boy dear ~ <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n05032o"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">A young man had come to the brethren to be prepared for baptism, it being their pious custom to receive youths under such circumstances. <mark>The soul of this particular young man was dear to St. Martin</mark>, and great was his grief when, on returning to the monastery after an absence of some two or three days, he was told that the lad had died suddenly. <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 33</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
